== Red Cabbage Slaw ==

In a #large bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and 1 1/2 tsp @sugar{1.5%tsp}. Season with a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} to bowl with dressing; toss to coat.

== Sloppy Joe Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @classic BBQ sauce{4%tablespoon}, @ketchup{2%tablespoon}, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and 1 TBSP @water{1%tbsp}.

> TIP: If you like a tangier BBQ sauce, add a small splash of vinegar if you have some left over.

== Turkey ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}, 1/4 tsp @salt{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until lightly browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add sauce to pan. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and turkey is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat. Season with @salt{} to taste.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, halve @potato buns{2%unit}; toast if desired.

Divide turkey filling and a spoonful of slaw between buns. Divide sloppy joes between plates. Serve with remaining slaw on the side.